content: I love love love this game! I've played it so many times, different paths of magic, different races native to this world, or just different choices! Each time it's like a new game. But when will volume/game/ come out? When I asked a few years ago, I was told the author was working on a book, I think, and WWU 3 would be out in a year or so. That was at least 4 years ago. Is it in the works? Thanks! I do love this game!
this is pathetically short. at least make the parts similar in length.

I really liked part one so I purchased part 2. This one was even better. I love how there are soooo many different ways you can play the MC. So many different choices through the game! Absolutely can't wait for part 3!!!
Felt a bit shorter than the first but thay could just be me being unable to stop playing
great story ... too bad part 3 never came out considering its been like 5 years now :/
i loved this game, and i hope a sequel is in the works...

I love this Choice game! I really wish they would come out with the 3rd installment! I'm dying to find out if the woman is guilty, or what happens to the vampire! Very engaging story and characters. I've played it numerous times with all the different "ways", hmm, except the healer...gotta go, new game to start!
I love this series so much and am anixously waiting for the squeal
gripping as hell

Love the game. But feel like some of the ways aren't really getting used much. I find that it seems like while your character is going through all this he isn't learning like he should or that some of the abilities aren't beimg used in their full potential. Like being able to see the future qhy can't you use that if the your character gets into a fight, like a quick glimpse into it. Also why can't your character be a specialised mage like Sem.
Amazing! Absolutely the best. I'll pay you more money - like a pre order fee or whatever if its gets more soon!

it's alright in that it is well written but there really isn't a lot of decisions to make or alot of major plot to be a part of. Feels more like it should have been a couple additional chapters to the first game as opposed to it's own game. Still like the series enough to buy #3 when I finally comes out.
Still holding out hope for 3!
Amazing cant wait for part 3 hopefully theres more choices to make

This sequel I feel is just as great as it's predecessor, it sucks you 
completely into a world where the story twists, turns and lands completely 
on it's head. This is definitely a series that I would refer to my friends
Love this game. The story continues ...can't wait to see what comes next!
Amazing! Waiting for chapter 3!
Love the story and looking forward to the conclusion!

I loved this series, good story, interesting character interactions and lore and alot to still learn. Through I hope the third one won't be the end for this series sense if you're character is in a grade system then why not continue the series all through those Tier grades , first, second and third Tier? Would make the series a more enjoyable series to play through and one I would spend my money on on each part. That's how much I love this series
I loved it too bad it never finished. Was one of my favorites.

The game is very good, I love all the choices and characters and the lore is very good lots of things help this world work. There is a problem though it's seems that the last game in this series seem like it wont come out some time
I like it but i feel like the first one had better options as far as character development.
Great Game  I hope there's more.

It was absolutely fantastic, just like the first one! But (spoiler alert), if you 'die' in the first game, you have speech problems in the second one. The only problem is, you only stutter during that one part. Maybe you should have it be throughout the game? That would make it be a little more like real life. Anyway, other than that, it was perfect! Please continue the series!
I liked how it was full of choices and the opportunities to mold your character into what you want. Kinda wish the story was continued though.

Tell the author to take his time not all things can be finished in a year but what you couldn't finish you make better make your primary objective to do better and succeed his story's are long just like lost heir they branch and  have a world and story to them instead of  being a 1 hit done they are a series a trilogy and that take true commitment and skill and a whole lot or lore now the 1 and done novels are also good just a quick story but it truly takes a lot of effort work and patience to create true lore a trilogy of lore. So good work to both publisher and author I look forward to the next one

When do you think number 3 will be out? In other words how long from now? Because I can't wait I love them so much I'm sitting there so happy for jun and so connected to my character love this series so much

Dumped by Jun and your friend Sem left you  ,  i cannot believe after reading half of the first part of the in darkness finally when the story picked up in second part it became depressing than ever, cant believe i paid for this
Terrific game, anxiously awaiting part 3.
This title is incomplete and was supposed to have a third installment in 2014. This shouldn't even be online and I want my money back!
This was sooo beautifully written i love the world you have created here. You have an amazing world here at you're fingertips.
Love it and will wait patiently for the next. Thanks to the author
Waited many years and the author clearly has no intention of finishing this series
Its been about three years now that I've been waiting for the third...wish it was out because I paid money for a story that's not even finished...
I invested in the series years ago with the promise of the finale coming soon. Too bad that wasn't true.

It's a really good game, I played the first one and it got me hooked. I was just wondering when the last installment will arrive? Is it because its bigger than the last two, or will it never come? Just wondering...
Loved this cant wait for the next. Ill probably buy it straght away
This is my favourite game. I was so desperate for more, as soon as I finished I bought the author's book on kindle, which is set in the same universe. Definitely worth the money x
Its been years!!
Plz hurry with next installment!!!!!
This is getting good and yet you end the story too soon where is part 3 and when is it coming out? I hope soon

Sadly I can't give this a good review because it actually ends in the middle of the story. I did enjoy the first Way Walkers, and also enjoyed this one, BUT it is a completely unfinished story. Part 1 came out in 2012 and this (part 2) came out almost exactly a year later. It has now been about 2 years and still no part 3, leading me to believe Way Walkers part 3 will never come out. So every single person who invested time into this story will likely never find out the ending. That's the reason for 1 star.
When is the final part going to be ready? I have been waiting for awhile now.  I have to say this is great, however the first part was better.

To potential readers - just buy it. You will play through numerous times and have fun. Costs less than a value meal to support someone's hard work and creativity. To the author - I hope you find your notebook. If you do not, then it is just another challenge to overcome. You are undoubtedly capable of fleshing out this great work to the fullest, and we all look forward to it.
Would very much like to complete it.
I enjoyed this
This adventure is fantastic, deep characters, choices that matter, and a universe that is completely fleshed out. Read the first one!

srry for bad english :)... This game is more like a novel than a choices game. I don't know how to explain it, but it makes me feel like I'm part of it rather than choose some choices, wait and see what happened. I like all characters in game (especially Sem lol). Hope for the next volume and thx you for this amazing work! d(^0^
One of my favorites from Hosted Games. Well worth a read. Well written, Enjoyed.
Put harry potter, dungeons and dragons, and many other iconic stuff and you will get this amazing series
This is my favorite choice game series of ALL time. I'm just dying of the wait for the next one.
I want my friend to get this so he Will understand how good it is. Kyle get this story
Loved it. Looking forward to the next installment
I can't wait for the next installment of WWU!!!
Really incredible game

This part of this texted based farce is not a complete story. It lacks  the slightest ounce of excitement and you'll swear your choices only really mean something if you play as a good Samaritan or the most evil loser to walk the face of whatever planet this "story" takes place on.
The storytelling is still flawless and the continuation is seamless. I hope the 3rd installment will come soon.
I have enjoyed reading the series so far I cannot wait for the finale
the best one!!!
Fantastic and I can't wait for the final
One of the better interactive stories out there. This one is even better then the first. Im looking forward to the next one. Keep it up!
Check out "King Of Awkwardtv" on YouTube for hilarious prank videos. So funny!!!
Tell me when the third one comes out cause I've been waiting for forever.
Can't wait for it
The I can't wait tell the next game comes put
I'll be sad when it's over though.
Wow this is getting better and better. Awaiting the last installment and hopefully it won't be last since this author makes great stories.

I loved this one as well; for being the second, or a continue, of a fantastic piece, this was lacking in nothing. The subtle change into "dating" was awesome, also, and didn't damper the excitement a bit. I am truly amazed, and I cannot wait for the third installment. I'm sure that it will be epic.
Gosh it's nearly may!  Hurry up with the next one please :-)
I literally spend hours playing this game and trying to find all the different paths. It is so much fun, but it will eat all of your time hahahaha

I've played all of the "choice of..." type games rated 4 stars or higher. This takes the cake. Best one yet. I'm so sad that part 3 isn't ready yet. I've spent so much time on these two games the past week. I can't wait for the finale. All the choices that didn't seem to have an effect in part 1 started showing in this one. The weaving really came out by the end.
Great game ;)
Very well done.

This game is amazing. The character all have amazing back story and the choices are thorough and vast enough that I could do whatever I wanted. The paths were surprising and gloriously written and I can't wait for the next installment!
Really enjoyed this release.  Can't wait for the next installment.  Sem is awesome.
Very little of the previous games choices have any bearing on the new one and its short.
Loved every second of it, can't wait to for the book to release.

I love everything about both parts of this story! From what I understand, the author is also going to release a novel set in this world. I plan to get the novel, along with any game sequels. Not only is the story line interesting and all the  potential characters fascinating, but the entire world has captured me! The ONLY way this author could improve on this game is technically - the italics and some grammar could be tweaked. Happy to give this 5 stars!

I've wanted to say so much about how wonderful this series is but honestly they're just aren't enough words to properly express my love. This is the series I suggest to get people into the genre. Dying for the next installment!
Glad I found part 2, I was going nuts...I love this game and Choice of the Vampire series...both compelling and fun! Hurry up with part 3...I rarely pay for an app, I pay for these!
unbelievably great
One of the best choice of games yet could not put it down for a second can't wait for the third installment keep them coming
Great series so far
better then the first still can't wait to see when we pick our ways and see what happens to illian
Its well worth paying for . The story sucks you in and leaves you dying to get the 3rd part

i found it a very good read its deffently in a league of its own copared to other choice games having endless choices which i found was't lacking compared to other choice games. the only drawback from this book that there is't really a fight or conflict that i found could really hurt me or kill me which i thouht was relly good from the first book . i did like the aspect of having a girlfriend it gives u a good choice in who to pick. Its cheper then a bag of chips so there should't be a reason not to buy it
I wouldnt want to rush greatness, but.. hurry with Part 3!   =)
Great part 2 story. It will be great if even longer pages. Keep it up
Dying for number 3!
A little short... but brilliant

Please make a part 3. Your a very good writer and I love the series so far and if its possible can you please make more choices & people ( like new in school but same grade). Like new person could try to steal you away (date you or make ypu cheat or something) from current bf or gf. Besides that its a 5 for me (:
I loved way walkers one and now this one is just as good, amazing. Perfect, long and so many ways to go I played it over and over again.
Yet another masterpiece, still able to astound us. With your dedication to detail to every decision it adds to your ability to make each one better then the last
I love this!!!
I waited so long for this second one.  Absolutely worth the wait.  I lived every second of it.  Great fantasy epic.
A truly great game. Very enjoyable and interesting world, as well as excellent characters.

I am incredibly excited to see the second part! And I can not wait for the third part, the second part does lack a bit of ehh explanation to some things, and since it will take a while for the.third part to be done, that some things should have been answered, though im sure most readers will re-read part to to re-ignite the curiosity when part three comes out. I think its well worth the money if not more, and i now rate J. Leigh with my favorite author, R.A Salvatore, and your a great inspiration so thanks.

Story is good. The problem is I don't like to switch to WWU1 when I want to restart from the begin. ZE I can play the whole story without switch to next part. Now I have to save everytime I go to WWU2. It's annoy.
It's a good story, but this part suffers a bit from bring part 2 in a trilogy. No real climax and a bit meandering  at times. Easily worth the money though, and I'm looking forward to the next part

Don't listen to the naysayers, this installment is perfectly awesome and left me looking forward to more. My character felt like he was much more useful and had a bigger impact on the storyline, and Can't wait for the next one.

Don't Expect any answers. Half the game the first was. I'd of rather Waited another year for a even halfway finished product. Was gonna buy book to but obviously author doesn't care about quality anymore only quantity. Do not buy it should be free.
#1 had great potential - this was a huge flop. Felt rushed, linear, lacked combat or even strong continuity. Very disappointed.
Finally it's here, I know how much I love the first one and I can't wait to read Way Walkers: University 2!
